reviews.text: If you're into beef, the signature tasting menu here is a must. I cannot think of a place comparable to this in terms of quality. My expectations were set high starting with a unique oolong tea from Taiwan and delicate starter dishes. The beef cuts were too special for heathens like me to cook myself so the trained staff sear it tableside, each piece exemplifying it's cut. Even the rice paired perfectly with the meat. It sounds over the top now that I'm writing it but it defies believability until one tries it. Compliments to the wait staff's attentive service and exemplary cooking. I will gladly come back here every chance I get.

Best Yaki Niku in Asia.  A great experience that leaves you refreshed/wowed after the meal unlike those greasy and fatty Yaki Niku experience found elsewhere.  A very good selection of beef and ingredients executed in a Japanese/French cuisine level of detail/perfection.  You will often see an elite crowd of customers ranging from celebrities, business tycoons to regional foodies/bloggers/chefs.  I am placing my bet that they will soon be crowned with the Michelin 1-2 stars next.  The owner is also a perfectionist with his food and wine choice.  His knowledge gives you the assurance that this is a place for those who appreciates the craft!
Definelty the best place to have Yakiniku quality beef. Worth going repeatedly. The owner handspick the meat in Japan and imports them from different regions.
Top Japanese restaurant! Super!!! Overpriced though...
